        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 29 at 1:25PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 125 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Rio Chiquito, or near Chimayo, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chimayo, Truchas, Rio Chiquito, Cundiyo, La Puebla, Cordova, Llano
and Llano Largo.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Heavy rains from severe thunderstorms can produce sudden and
dangerous flows in arroyos, ditches and over low water crossings. Do
not attempt to drive through areas where water covers the roadway.</instruction>
